            <abstract><p>His daughter [Mariamne Johnes] continues to be treated with blisters but they are causing more irritation than they should as Mr Williams is not attending them as he should, and she cannot wear the stays so cannot walk.</p><p>His anxiety over possibility of having to go to Ireland [Irish Rebellion of 1798] with his regiment, which offered to go without consulting him, an action he does not understand.</p></abstract>
